05/09/2003
KRAKOW, Poland -- During their meeting on Thursday (4 September), President Aleksander Kwasniewski and his counterparts from Croatia, Macedonia and Romania agreed that Europe should provide a good example and eliminate ethnic conflicts and extreme differences between rich and poor. The four presidents met within the framework of the 13th Krynica economic forum. They stressed that support should be provided to countries that have not yet joined NATO or the EU. (Rzeczpospolita - 05/09/03; Polish Radio 1, Rompres, HINA, BBC - 04/09/03)
